<br>
Unfortunuately the knockback is so slight that virtually everyone 50+ will channel through most of the hits (unless you're fighting underwater).<br>
<br>
I wouldn't even bother nuking a cleric.  Bring crystallized pumice (or golem rods) and be ready to dispell your pet when you see that fear effect coming from the cleric.  You'll just have to try and run them out of mana.<br>
<br>
Melees are a question of speed.  If they run faster than you, you die.  If not, you can win.  Use external camera views to keep an eye on them while you run in circles to avoid them and let the pet hit them.  Basically just stay out of melee range and let the pet beat on them.  Do not try to channel through any hits.  Even if it works, it's not worth it.  If it's a 54+ warrior with low hit points, let the pet finish him.  Stop and nuke only if he stops trying to follow you, and even then, be ready to run again if he turns on you (don't try to channel!).<br>
<br>
This is why I buy SOW potions in bulk.  I'm never without SOW in PvP.  SOW &gt; Jboots, though having jboots is nice too.<br>
